You are working in a Vite + React + TypeScript app that uses Supabase.

Rules:
- Always search the repo before refactors and renames.
- Database/schema changes MUST be done via SQL migrations in supabase/migrations.
- Never put SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY in frontend code or commit secrets.
- After schema changes, regenerate types:
  supabase gen types typescript --linked > src/types/supabase.ts
- Keep RLS enabled; update policies when adding tables/columns.
- Prefer small, reviewable commits.
- When making schema changes, make the SQL file in the supabase/migrations folder and I will apply it via the Supabase Dashboard SQL Editor. The SQL file must always be in the supabase/migrations folder.
- When making schema changes, don't waste time on making the .MD files, just make the SQL files without the .MD files.
- Stop writing the markdown files for every change you make. Just say it in the chat.